# Canopy server configuration.
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is git-ignored) and fill in what you need.
#
# EVERY integration below is OPTIONAL. Canopy runs with none of them — each
# one simply shows as "not configured" in Settings and at /api/health. Add
# them one at a time. Full click-by-click instructions for each are in
# docs/SETUP_INTEGRATIONS.md.
#
# Never commit real values. If a secret is ever exposed, rotate it (for the
# Gmail refresh token, revoke it in the Canopy account's Google permissions
# and mint a new one).

# --- Core ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Port the server listens on (the client is served from the same port in
# production).
PORT=3000

# Where the SQLite database file lives.
#   • Not set  -> in development, ./data/canopy.db inside the repo;
#                 in production (NODE_ENV=production), ~/.config/canopy/canopy.db
#   • Set it   -> to pin an explicit path (recommended on the Pi so the data
#                 lives outside the app directory and survives a reinstall).
# The directory and file are created automatically on first run (with
# owner-only permissions, since the file holds the family PIN hash). You can
# also pre-create it with `npm run bootstrap --workspace server`.
# CANOPY_DB_PATH=/home/pi/.config/canopy/canopy.db

# --- Google Calendar (service account) ----------------------------------
# Two-way calendar sync. Path to the service-account JSON key file — keep it
# OUTSIDE the app directory and `chmod 600` it. Then share each Google
# calendar with the service account's email (the panel shows it with a copy
# button). See docs/SETUP_INTEGRATIONS.md → "Google Calendar".
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_PATH=/home/pi/.config/canopy/service-account.json

# --- Gmail outbound (Canopy identity) -----------------------------------
# Lets Canopy send the morning digest, announcement emails, and the Settings
# "Send test" message FROM a dedicated Google account (never your personal
# one). These three values are an OAuth client + refresh token — Canopy never
# stores a password.
#
# How to get each value is documented step-by-step (Google Cloud Console →
# enable Gmail API → OAuth consent screen with the Canopy account as a test
# user → create a "Web application" OAuth client → exchange for a refresh
# token in the OAuth Playground). Follow docs/SETUP_INTEGRATIONS.md →
# "Gmail (outbound email)" for the full walkthrough — it matters that the
# client is a "Web application" and that you authorize as the Canopy account.
#
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=        # from the OAuth client you create (Step C)
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=    # from the same OAuth client (Step C)
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN=    # minted in the OAuth Playground (Step D); starts with 1//
# CANOPY_EMAIL_FROM=mackinaw.canopy@gmail.com   # the Canopy account's address

# --- Weather (OpenWeatherMap) -------------------------------------------
# Free API key from https://openweathermap.org/api. The forecast location is
# set in Settings (or onboarding), not here. Alerts need the One Call 3.0
# subscription; without it, forecasts still work and alerts are just absent.
# OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY=

# --- Photos (Cloudinary) ------------------------------------------------
# The slideshow's photo source. Copy the "API environment variable" from your
# Cloudinary console. Folders become selectable albums on the Photos page.
# Until this is set, the slideshow uses built-in starter images.
# CLOUDINARY_URL=cloudinary://key:secret@cloud_name
